    "what_description": "Pyrostria verdcourtii is an evergreen shrub or small tree belonging to the family Rubiaceae. It is characterized by its glabrous or pubescent stems, which can grow up to 4 meters in height, and its ovate to elliptic leaves that are 2-6 centimeters long and have a cuneate base. The leaves are opposite, with a pair of glands at the base, and are glabrous or pubescent on the lower surface. Pyrostria verdcourtii produces white or cream-colored flowers in clusters, which are 2-3 centimeters in diameter, and have a calyx with five lobes. The flowers are followed by red or orange berries, 1-2 centimeters in diameter, which contain 4-8 seeds.",
